title: More than 200 injured after makeshift gallery of football stadium collapses in Kerala - Times of India
content:
1. More than 200 injured after makeshift gallery of football stadium collapses in Kerala  Times of India
  2. 200 people injured as temporary gallery collapses in Malappuram, Kerala  ThePrint
  3. 200 injured, 5 critical after makeshift gallery collapse in Kerala  Kalinga TV
  4. Watch: Spectator Gallery Collapses At Kerala Match, Over 200 Injured  NDTV
  5. Makeshift gallery at football ground collapses in Kerala's Malappuram; Around 200 injured  Hindustan Times
  6. View Full coverage on Google News
description: The incident took place at around 9 pm when a football final match was being played in Poongodu, a football crazy village near Wandoor and Kalikavu. The police said that all the injured people were taken to nearby hospitals. Five people are said to be in serious condition.
